# secrets — API keys live here, never publish
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Shell-quoting artefacts. An unquoted redirect or heredoc inside a `node -e`
# one-liner makes the shell treat a fragment of the code as a filename, dropping
# an empty file named e.g. `false)`, `{,`, `c[s]` or `console.log(` in the repo
# root. Five of these reached this public repo once already. These patterns are
# root-anchored so they can never hide a real source file under src/.
#
# Shape alone cannot catch every case — an artefact that happens to be a bare
# identifier (`EquationQuestion`, `i`, `0`) is indistinguishable from a real
# filename — so the standing rule matters more than the patterns: in this repo
# never run `git add -A`. Use `git add -u` plus explicit paths.
/*(*
/*)*
/*\[*
/*]*
/*{*
/*}*
/*`*
/*$*

# local tooling / assistant config — never publish
.claude/
.mcp.json

